The introductory MA seminar introduces the possibilities of the specialities and the curriculum as a whole, the principles of work of the graduate schools and options available within them, possible practical training options and advises students in the choice of the supervisor. It introduces the requirements set for MA theses/MA projects in the speciality and the general process of writing a MA thesis/MA project. The introductory MA seminar supports students in their choice of the supervisor and the general research topic. The introductory seminar builds a basis for interdisciplinary seminars.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce the possibilities of the specialities and the curriculum as a whole, the principles of work of the graduate schools and options available within them, possible practical training options and to advise students in the choice of the supervisor. To introduce the requirements set for MA theses/MA projects in the speciality and the general process of writing a MA thesis/MA project. After the introductory MA seminar students are able to choose their supervisor and the general research topic. The introductory seminar builds a basis for interdisciplinary seminars.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students understand the options available within their speciality, curriculum and the graduate schools of the Faculty of Philosophy. Students understand the requirements set for MA theses/MA projects within their speciality and are able to choose a topic area and supervisor from the options available within the speciality.
